parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Transmission failure can cause the vehicle to hesitate, jerk, or fail to move, leading to accidents or leaving the driver stranded. In some cases, it may also cause the vehicle to lose power or become difficult to control.
symptoms: The vehicle hesitates or jerks when accelerating
the vehicle fails to move forward or reverse
warning lights and errors appear on the dashboard
the transmission gear changes at the wrong RPM

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Torque converter failure can cause the transmission to malfunction, leading to hesitation, jerking, or failure to move, which can result in accidents or leave the driver stranded.
symptoms: The transmission torque converter clutch is not operating as expected
the transmission is not shifting properly
the vehicle hesitates or jerks when accelerating

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The lack of transmission maintenance can lead to premature transmission failure, causing the vehicle to hesitate, jerk, or fail to move, which can result in accidents or leave the driver stranded.
symptoms: The transmission does not have a dipstick to check the fluid level
the dealership does not provide information on transmission fluid changes

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Transmission failure can cause loss of power, difficulty accelerating, and potentially lead to accidents or fires.
symptoms: hesitation or delay in shifting gears
unusual noises or vibrations from the transmission.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Engine or cooling system failure can cause overheating, loss of power, and potentially lead to fires.
symptoms: Unusual fumes or smoke from the engine

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Loss of vehicle control can lead to accidents, injuries, and fatalities.
symptoms: failure to respond to steering input.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the pre-collision assist system can cause the vehicle to hesitate or fail to accelerate properly, leading to potential accidents or loss of control.
symptoms: The dashboard indicator displays "Pre-Collision Assist Not Available"
the vehicle hesitates or fails to accelerate
the vehicle shakes back and forth
and the vehicle may not respond to accelerator pedal input.
